	<ul class="comments" id="comments">
	  		
			<li>
<div class='comment-container' id='comment-15584' style='background-color:rgb(255,255,255)'>
<a name='comment-15584'></a>
<div class='user-info'>
<div class='screenname'>
<a href="http://www.splicetoday.com/profile/armchairpunter">armchairpunter</a>
</div>
<div class='date'>Nov 11, 2011, 10:59AM</div>
</div>
<p>Seems strange to single out the (unjustifiably) dismissive response of some Cain boosters to the serious allegations that have emerged without also reminding the reader of the manner in which wagons were circled around our 42nd President.</p>
</div>
</li>
<li>
<div class='comment-container' id='comment-15585' style='background-color:rgb(228,229,230)'>
<a name='comment-15585'></a>
<div class='user-info'>
<div class='screenname'>
<a href="http://www.splicetoday.com/profile/andrew">andrew</a>
</div>
<div class='date'>Nov 11, 2011, 11:44AM</div>
</div>
<p>Oh please, punter. Clinton was impeached by the House, and even some Democrats voted with Republicans. He came within spitting distance of being removed from office (while Speaker Gingrich cheated on his wife, amirite?). Cain is still the frontrunner by a few points. But by all means, go ahead and trot out every last example of less-than-perfect responses to sexual harassment. Which proves...what, exactly?</p>
</div>
</li>
<li>
<div class='comment-container' id='comment-15586' style='background-color:rgb(255,255,255)'>
<a name='comment-15586'></a>
